    "causasEn": "Causes are classified as antepartum, intrapartum, and neonatal. Antepartum causes include placental insufficiency, placental abruption, severe preeclampsia, complicated maternal diabetes, severe fetal anemia, and congenital infections. Intrapartum causes include shoulder dystocia, umbilical cord prolapse, uterine rupture, difficult instrumental delivery, complicated breech presentation, true cord knots, and prolonged cord compression. Neonatal causes include congenital airway malformations, congenital diaphragmatic hernia, respiratory failure of any cause, and congenital heart disease with severe hemodynamic compromise. In many cases, asphyxia results from a combination of antepartum and intrapartum factors.",
