    "prevencionEn": "Prevention of perinatal asphyxia requires adequate prenatal surveillance, including fetal monitoring during labor (cardiotocography), early identification of high-risk pregnancies, and delivery care by personnel trained in neonatal resuscitation. Timely access to emergency cesarean section when indicated is fundamental. All delivery room personnel should be trained in the Neonatal Resuscitation Program (NRP) and resuscitation equipment must be available and verified before every birth. Prevention of prematurity, adequate management of preeclampsia and gestational diabetes, and avoiding prolonged pregnancies also contribute to reducing risk.",
    "consejosParaPadresEs": "Si su bebe ha sufrido asfixia perinatal, es probable que necesite tratamiento en la UCIN. La hipotermia terapeutica puede ser dificil de comprender: su bebe estara en una manta de enfriamiento y puede verse palido o tener cambios en el color de la piel, lo cual es parte del tratamiento. Pregunte al equipo medico que pueden hacer por su bebe, incluyendo hablarle suavemente y el contacto cuando sea medicamente apropiado. Es importante entender que la evolucion neurologica se evalua a lo largo del tiempo, y los primeros dias no siempre predicen el desenlace final. Solicite informacion sobre los programas de seguimiento del neurodesarrollo disponibles. No dude en buscar apoyo emocional y psicologico; esta es una experiencia extremadamente dificil para las familias.",
    "consejosParaPadresEn": "If your baby has suffered perinatal asphyxia, they will likely need treatment in the NICU. Therapeutic hypothermia can be difficult to understand: your baby will be on a cooling blanket and may look pale or have changes in skin color, which is part of the treatment. Ask the medical team what you can do for your baby, including speaking softly and providing contact when medically appropriate. It is important to understand that neurological evolution is assessed over time, and the first few days do not always predict the final outcome. Request information about available neurodevelopmental follow-up programs. Do not hesitate to seek emotional and psychological support; this is an extremely difficult experience for families.",
